			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Viddler&#39;s rapid growth requires the addition of a Vertical &amp; Partner Marketing (VPM) Manager.</p>
<p>
<br />
The right person for this newly created position will be charged with expanding, and formalizing Viddler&#39;s 3rd party partner network of software developers and video solution services providers.&nbsp;&nbsp; The VPM will also lead the development and establishment of &quot;total product solutions&quot; for Viddler&#39;s served and emerging vertical markets.&nbsp;&nbsp; VPM compensation is tied to the Viddler top line revenue in order to assure that members exceed the Viddler 2013 Revenue forecast. Other duties:</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
The VPM must be fluent / knowledgeable with unmet needs and opportunities relating to each partner/industry group in order to assure maximal success and mindshare from all efforts and programs designed</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
The VPM collaborates with vertical market leaders and partner leaders in order to assure a clear maximum value proposition for each group; so that Viddler&rsquo;s products deliver a total product solution to each respective industry group</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
The VPN will meet regularly with prospective partners and vertical markets influencers to maintain the insights, knowledge and efficacy of all programs</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Application of duties and responsibilities:</strong></p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
&bull; Target, author, build and manage all deliverables for each targeted group</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
&bull; Ensure that Viddler internal sales team and Viddler channel partners are equipped with all the information, materials, landing pages, promotions, etc., necessary to establish respective vertical and or partner success</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
&bull; Develop and specify content for creation of product related marketing collateral necessary to recruit partners as well as end user prospects</p>
<p>
<br />
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
&bull; On Line Video Industry knowledge; capable of early recognition of industry trends</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
&bull; Minimum 3 years product management, project mangement, and &nbsp;prioritization of tasks</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
&bull; Customer aware (Experience as a customer a plus)</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
&bull; Strong knowledge of web based sales and marketing strategies</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
&bull; Capable of hi-level interation with customers/prospects, industry analysts, &amp; industry media&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-left: 40px;">
<br />
&bull; Hands on experience in channel or partner network marketing desirable</p>
